results.title: Sand Surfing in Um Al Oush: 12/10/2018am
results.description:
A Friday morning cruise around the spectacular sands of Umm al Oush to practice and develop Advance level skills.

Dear Members, Please be reminded that as an Advance drive this is trip is NOT open to any driver below the advance level.

Trip limited to a maximum of 5 Advance drivers.

results.title: Wadi Shwaka Revisited
results.description:
Relaxing and relatively moderate to easy rock crawling trip in Wadi Shawka area for those who like such type of terrain.

Be ready for a full day of a different type of fun.

Please bring enough food and drinks for you and your passengers, your camera and garbage bags so we do not throw our garbage on the trail. 

 

Meeting will be ADNOC Sharjah Kalba Road  found on the following link

https://goo.gl/maps/UqctvfKtRBn

results.name: Clear Communication
results.description:
Member demonstrates clear and controlled 
communication skills including proper radio discipline.

results.name: Cresting Small Dunes
results.description:
Member can safely crest small dunes straight with 
proper amount of power and control (without jumping or launching)

results.name: Cresting Medium Dunes
results.description:
Member can safely crest medium dunes straight 
on with proper amount of power and control (without jumping or launching)

results.name: Descend Small Slip-face
results.description:
Member can safely descend a small slip-face in 
a controlled manner.

results.name: Descend Medium Slipface
results.description:
Member can safely descend a medium sized 
slipface in a controlled manner.

results.name: Basic Side Sloping
results.description:
Member can safely side slope small dunes in a 
controlled manner and know when to turn down - not fighting gravity.

results.name: Basic Recovery
results.description: Perform basic snatch recovery under the supervision of a Marshal demonstrating proper position, clear communication, safe equipment uses and vehicle control.

results.name: Crest and Descend Large dunes
results.description: Member can safely crest large dunes and descend large slipface with proper amount of power and control.

results.name: Side Cresting Small Dunes
results.description: Member can safely crest a dune at an angle other than straight on in a variety of different scenarios in a safe and controlled manner appropriate for their vehicle.

results.name: Enter and Exit Bowls
results.description: Member can safely enter and exit small and large bowls with proper amount of power and control.

results.name: Side Sloping
results.description: Member can safely side slope in a controlled manner and know when to turn down - not fighting gravity.

results.name: GPS
results.description: Member can record waypoints on their GPS.

results.name: Fix Pop out
results.description: Member can safely manage the repair of a tire Pop out.

results.name: Introduction to Night Drive
results.description: Member to be able to drive safely at night (after sunset)

results.name: Side Cresting Big Dunes
results.description: Member can safely crest a dune at an angle other than straight on in a variety of different scenarios in a safe and controlled manner appropriate for their vehicle.

results.name: Advance Recovery
results.description: Member can safely manage all aspects of an advance recovery under the supervision of a Marshal demonstrating proper safety assessment and position, clear communication, safe equipment uses and vehicle control. An Advance Recovery is a recovery that cannot be pulled straight on or is performed on a steep slope or angle.

results.name: Winch Recovery
results.description: Member can safely manage all aspects of a winch recovery and/or support winch recovery under the supervision of a Marshal demonstrating proper safety assessment and position, clear communication and safe equipment use.

results.name: Navigation
results.description: Member can confidently and safely navigate using (GAIA/Garmin or others) to define points and a safe exit point during day or night drives, program waypoints into their GPS (different format) and use the GPS to navigate to a waypoint (Pass “GPS Trip”).

results.name: Second Leading
results.description: Member can safely perform the role of second lead in various levels, stopping the convoy if the leading Marshal discovers an unknown hazard, rerouting the convoy at the leading marshal’s direction and assisting the leading Marshal with managing the convoy.

results.name: Sweeping
results.description:
Member can safely perform the role of sweeper in a trip, 
keeping the leading Marshal aware of any problems or stuck in the convoy and 
coordinating any recoveries with the leading Marshal.

response.title: Central Motors & Equipment
response.description: Central Motors & Equipment LLC (CM&E) is a Member of ALFAHIM Automotive, providing diversified range of products, services & solutions to cater the dynamic market needs of the UAE whether in retail or wholesales through its exclusive distribution rights of world renowned brands such as Bosch, Michelin, Osram, Knorr-Bremse, Valeo, Dremel, TIGAR and many more in the country with its purpose built and state of the art facilities.

response.title: Eastern Motors
response.description: Alfahim introduced Eastern Motors to be the first ever automotive mall concept in the Emirate of Abu Dhabi. Located in the oasis city of Al Ain, and strategically located in Al Saniya District, Eastern Motors provides clients with an all-round automotive experience which includes Mercedes-Benz, Jeep, Fiat, Mopar, Michelin, Tyre Plus and Bosch.
